editorialNotes.standard: Slide a shape into the correct holeâeasy, right? It is, at first. From shape-changing to colour-mixing to hidden holes, weâre impressed with how the gameplay spurs out-of-the-box thinking, stimulating curious young minds.

What are those towers that touch the sky? Tinybopâs awesome sandbox teaches kids the fun wayâby letting them build, watch, and play. As they add floors and test the effects of plumbing problems and earthquakes, they're actually learning basic design and engineering principles. editorialNotes.standard: Bursting with beats and energy, Toca Dance will make the whole family want to get up and groove. This incredibly cute game puts kids in charge of their own musical productionâchoosing dancers, costumes and techno tracks, and choreographing moves using simple swipes and taps. Once the performance starts, the real fun begins: you can fling items at the stage, set off pyrotechnics and other cool effects and even cheer (or boo) your squad. Seeing the payoffâan awesome video you can shareâwill encourage players to jump right back in and start working on their next great show.

Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivatedâand Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new âdos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.
